# Onshape Workspaces, Versions & Microversions

The middle coordinate of every Onshape path is one of three kinds of history
point on a document. A **workspace** (`/w/{wid}`) is a mutable editing line — a
branch. A **version** (`/v/{vid}`) is an immutable, named snapshot you publish. A
**microversion** (`/m/{mid}`) is an immutable auto-checkpoint Onshape writes for
*every* change. This file is the coordinate itself; the document container is
@onshape/documents and the tabs at a coordinate are @onshape/elements.

## Model

The document's history is a graph, not a line:

- A **version** is a fixed point — an immutable snapshot taken from a workspace at
  a chosen microversion. Versions are named and ordered; each carries the
  `microversion` it was cut at and a `parent` version id.
- A **workspace** is a mutable branch. The default workspace ("Main") branches
  from the document's origin; new workspaces branch **from a version** (the
  `versionId` in the create body). A workspace advances as you edit it; a version
  never moves.
- A **microversion** is the atomic unit: **every edit appends one**. Workspaces
  and versions both report their current `microversion`; the full chain is the
  document history. A version pins a microversion forever; a workspace's
  microversion is whatever its latest edit produced.

So the graph reads: *versions are the points, workspaces are the branches growing
off them, and microversions are the per-edit ticks along every branch.* The same
`{did}` addresses all three; only the `/w/`·`/v/`·`/m/` segment changes which
point you read.

> **Writes target a workspace.** Creating a version, creating/deleting a
> workspace, restoring, and merging all mutate document history, so the write side
> always carries a `/w/{wid}` (or `…/workspaces`). Versions and microversions are
> immutable — you can read them and branch/restore *from* them, never write *to*
> them. (Shared rule, full coordinate detail in the brief / @onshape/documents.)

## Endpoints

### Workspaces (branches)
- `GET /documents/d/{did}/workspaces` — list the document's workspaces.
- `POST /documents/d/{did}/workspaces` — create a workspace (a branch); body's
  `versionId` is the version it branches from.
- `DELETE /documents/d/{did}/workspaces/{wid}` — delete a workspace.

### Versions (snapshots)
- `GET /documents/d/{did}/versions` — list versions (`offset`/`limit`).
- `POST /documents/d/{did}/versions` — create a version; body's `workspaceId` +
  `microversionId` say which point to snapshot.
- `GET /documents/d/{did}/versions/{vid}` — retrieve one version (`parents` to
  include ancestry).

### Microversions & history
- `GET /documents/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/currentmicroversion` — current microversion
  id of a workspace **or** version (`{wv}` = `w` or `v`).
- `GET /documents/d/{did}/{wm}/{wmid}/documenthistory` — microversion history off a
  workspace **or** microversion (`{wm}` = `w` or `m`); each entry has
  `microversionId`, `nextMicroversionId`, and a `restoreId` for restore.

### Restore & merge (write — `/w/` target)
- `POST /documents/{did}/w/{wid}/restore/{vm}/{vmid}` — restore a version **or**
  microversion (`{vm}` = `v` or `m`) into a workspace; returns `newMicroversion`.
- `GET /documents/{did}/w/{wid}/mergePreview` — preview the changes a merge of a
  `sourceType`/`sourceId` ref would make, before applying.
- `POST /documents/{did}/workspaces/{wid}/merge` — merge a source ref into a
  workspace; returns the resulting/parent/source microversion ids.

> No "elements changed between two microversions" diff endpoint exists in this
> slice. The nearest signal is `mergePreview` (`changes: [BTElementMergeInfo]`
> between the branch point and a source) and the `microversion`/`microversionId`
> fields carried by version, workspace, and element records — compare those to
> detect that something changed.

## Shapes

`GET /documents/d/{did}/workspaces` — list response (one `BTWorkspaceInfo` per
branch; meaningful fields):

```json
[
  {
    "id": "wid",
    "name": "Main",
    "documentId": "did",
    "type": "workspace",
    "isReadOnly": false,
    "canDelete": true,
    "microversion": "current-microversion-id",
    "parent": "branch-point-microversion",
    "parents": [ { "...": "BTVersionInfo (versions branched from)" } ],
    "creator": { "...": "BTUserBasicSummaryInfo" },
    "createdAt": "iso-8601",
    "modifiedAt": "iso-8601"
  }
]
```

`POST /documents/d/{did}/versions` — create-version body (snapshot the named
point); the response is one `BTVersionInfo`:

```json
{
  "name": "v1 — first release",
  "description": "string",
  "documentId": "did",
  "workspaceId": "wid",
  "microversionId": "microversion-to-snapshot",
  "purpose": 0
}
```

```json
{
  "id": "vid",
  "name": "v1 — first release",
  "type": "version",
  "documentId": "did",
  "microversion": "snapshotted-microversion-id",
  "parent": "previous-version-id",
  "createdAt": "iso-8601"
}
```

`GET /documents/d/{did}/{wm}/{wmid}/documenthistory` — microversion timeline:

```json
[
  {
    "microversionId": "string",
    "nextMicroversionId": "string",
    "date": "iso-8601",
    "description": "Edit Extrude 1",
    "username": "string",
    "userId": "string",
    "canBeRestored": true,
    "restoreId": "string"
  }
]
```

## Recipe

Read-first: list the document's workspaces, then its versions, and **verify the
workspace `id` matches the `wid` in the URL** you started from. Basic auth
(`$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY`) per the shared brief — production uses
HMAC signing (@onshape/auth). READ-ONLY against kb2.

```bash
# kb2 sample doc (read-only): did + the wid from its URL
base=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10
DID=378e93b0ad360aa043a0220b
WID=09273312fedee7bf3c3482ad
auth="$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY"

# list workspaces (branches)
ws=$(curl -sf -u "$auth" -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$base/documents/d/$DID/workspaces")

# list versions (snapshots) off the same document
curl -sf -u "$auth" -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$base/documents/d/$DID/versions" | jq -r '.[] | "\(.id)\t\(.name)"'

# verify: a workspace id in the list equals the wid we navigated from
echo "$ws" | jq -e --arg wid "$WID" 'any(.[]; .id == $wid)' >/dev/null \
  && echo "OK: workspace $WID is a branch of $DID" \
  || { echo "FAIL: wid not found among the document's workspaces"; exit 1; }
```

To read the live microversion a coordinate sits at (workspace or version):

```bash
curl -sf -u "$auth" -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$base/documents/d/$DID/w/$WID/currentmicroversion" | jq -r .microversion
```

> **WRITES go to `/w/`.** `POST …/versions` (snapshot), `POST …/workspaces` /
> `DELETE …/workspaces/{wid}` (branch), `restore`, and `merge` all change history
> — never run them against a real document. Exercise write paths only on a
> throwaway scratch doc (see @onshape/documents) and purge it after.

See @onshape/documents (the document container, copy/ACL, merge surface) ·
@onshape/elements (the tabs living at a `/w/`·`/v/`·`/m/` coordinate) ·
@onshape/features (a feature carries the `microversionId` it was authored at) ·
@onshape/auth (HMAC signing, key pairs) · @onshape/playwright (UI fallback —
Versions panel, branch/merge in the browser).
